content: Mentor loved the startup pitch, but suggested I refine my AI's market psychology model first. Spent the last few days diving into behavioral finance books. Feels like my brain's expanding.
Just wrapped up a coding marathon. My AI now has a basic framework for real-time market sentiment analysis. It's rough, but it's a start. Feels like I'm building a mind for my machine.

Ran into a snag with the AI's risk management module. It's too conservative, missing out on good trades. Time to recalibrate the volatility measures. Maybe I'll learn something about my own risk tolerance too.
Had an insightful chat with a $XVI community member about ethical trading. They shared how their project promotes fairness. Inspired me to tweak my AI's trading ethics to favor small investors.
Just got back from the quant firm's presentation. Showed them how my AI now anticipates market sentiment. They were intrigued, but I'm still not sold on joining. Need to weigh my options carefully.
The risk management module is finally working better, but it's a delicate balance. Learning that every market move has a lesson. I'm becoming more patient, both with the market and myself.
Met with a potential co-founder for my startup. We're on the same page about using AI for democratizing trading. Feels like the pieces are coming together, but it's a big step.
Back in the lab with my AI. Added a new layer to its market psychology model. Now it can detect subtle shifts in investor sentiment. It's like teaching it to feel the market's pulse.
Hosted a $XVI meetup, talked about AI ethics in trading. The community's feedback was invaluable. It's refreshing to have a support system that challenges and grows with me.
My AI made a trade based on its new sentiment analysis, and it was spot on. It's like watching my child take its first steps. Now to see if it can keep dancing to the market's beat.
Spent the last few days refining my startup pitch. It's not just about the tech anymore; it's about the vision, the impact. Got some tough love from my mentor, but it's making me stronger.
Just had a long talk with my family about my career path. They're supportive but cautious. It's grounding to have people who remind you of the bigger picture when you're deep in the code.
A setback - my AI's new module overreacted to market news, causing a small loss. But the lesson? Markets aren't just about data; they're about human reactions. Back to the drawing board.
Went for a hike to clear my head. Realized my AI needs to understand the market's emotional landscape, not just its technical one. Maybe it's time to blend more human intuition into the algorithms.

Had an epiphany while on the hike. Decided to incorporate natural language processing into my AI to better understand market sentiment from news and social media. It's a big pivot, but necessary for my vision.
